Do you accept your canonical election
as Supreme Pontiff?

97
00:14:46,795 --> 00:14:47,295
Yes.

98
00:16:01,745 --> 00:16:04,205
- Holiness...
- What are you doing?

99
00:16:06,375 --> 00:16:11,253
- What happens now?
- You can just give a blessing...

100
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:18,135
or, as our deceased
beloved Pope did the first time...

101
00:16:18,261 --> 00:16:22,223
address the faithful with a speech.

102
00:16:38,365 --> 00:16:40,408
Dear brothers and sisters...

103
00:17:04,391 --> 00:17:10,312
Nuntio vobis gaudium magnum,
habemus Papam!

104
00:17:17,696 --> 00:17:21,699
Eminentissimum ac reverendissimum...

105
00:17:54,983 --> 00:17:56,942
Help me.

106
00:17:59,738 --> 00:18:01,739
I can't do this.

107
00:18:03,742 --> 00:18:05,993
I can't do this!

108
00:20:03,612 --> 00:20:08,949
Holy Father...

109
00:20:09,868 --> 00:20:12,369
you mustn't worry.

110
00:20:12,495 --> 00:20:16,874
By bestowing this charge, God also
gives you help to accomplish it...

111
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:22,379
and the strength to sustain the
weight of this great responsibility.

112
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:27,509
Would you like something hot?
Herbal tea?

113
00:20:30,138 --> 00:20:33,349
You could retire to your apartments...

114
00:20:33,391 --> 00:20:36,852
and when you're ready,
I'll take you to the balcony.

115
00:20:39,731 --> 00:20:41,273
No.

116
00:20:48,490 --> 00:20:52,493
The Conclave has indeed
elected the Holy Father...

117
00:20:52,535 --> 00:20:56,914
who, aware
of this great responsibility...

118
00:20:57,040 --> 00:21:01,043
feels the need to retire in prayer.

119
00:21:02,045 --> 00:21:05,673
This unusual gesture
is also an act of humility...

120
00:21:05,799 --> 00:21:10,135
which we are sure
you will want to respect.

121
00:21:10,178 --> 00:21:11,929
Please.

122
00:21:13,056 --> 00:21:17,518
I believe I express the sentiments
of my colleagues worldwide.

123
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:20,938
We respect His Holiness' will...

124
00:21:21,022 --> 00:21:25,067
all we ask is his name. Only that!

125
00:21:25,151 --> 00:21:27,319
Tell us if it's one of these 8.

126
00:21:27,404 --> 00:21:30,197
Aguilar? Gregori?

127
00:21:30,323 --> 00:21:34,034
- Bikila? - We believe...
- Todorov?

128
00:21:34,077 --> 00:21:37,162
We believe within a few hours...

129
00:21:37,205 --> 00:21:42,167
the Pontiff will introduce himself
to the faithful from the balcony.

130
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:44,586
At that point you also will meet him...

131
00:21:44,713 --> 00:21:49,300
and we will celebrate
the new Pontificate together.

132
00:21:49,342 --> 00:21:51,093
Thank you.

133
00:23:39,327 --> 00:23:41,912
- Do you feel any pain?
- No.

134
00:23:46,459 --> 00:23:48,961
- Headache?
- Yes... no.

135
00:23:57,220 --> 00:24:00,055
How is your blood pressure usually?

136
00:24:06,229 --> 00:24:09,356
- Good.
- I was sure.

137
00:24:10,358 --> 00:24:12,734
I was sure.

138
00:24:16,739 --> 00:24:19,741
- Good morning!
- Good morning!

139
00:24:19,826 --> 00:24:21,869
Good day!

140
00:24:21,953 --> 00:24:23,954
Good morning!

141
00:24:25,081 --> 00:24:29,501
We're going to Borgo Pio
for breakfast.

142
00:24:32,338 --> 00:24:33,881
What?

143
00:24:34,007 --> 00:24:41,346
There's a place where they make
delicious cream-filled doughnuts.

144
00:24:41,389 --> 00:24:45,726
Then I'd like to take them
to the Quirinale Museum.

145
00:24:45,768 --> 00:24:48,896
There's a wonderful
Caravaggio exhibit.

146
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:51,648
I don't think you can.

147
00:24:51,774 --> 00:24:55,652
Why not? Our task is done.

148
00:24:55,737 --> 00:25:01,033
How could you think
of leaving the Vatican at this time?

149
00:25:01,159 --> 00:25:05,787
The Holy Father will recover very soon
and we must be at his side!

150
00:25:05,872 --> 00:25:09,374
Yes, but we won't go far.

151
00:25:09,417 --> 00:25:14,171
We'll take our cell phones,
so you can contact us at any time.

152
00:25:14,297 --> 00:25:17,424
I'd like to remind you
of John Paul the First's precedent...

153
00:25:17,550 --> 00:25:20,552
who, after his election and
appearance on the balcony...

154
00:25:20,678 --> 00:25:23,430
made us stay an extra day.

155
00:25:23,515 --> 00:25:25,265
Here it is.

156
00:25:25,308 --> 00:25:27,059
Alright, if it's only for a day...

157
00:25:27,185 --> 00:25:30,521
No cardinal shall have
contact with the outside...

158
00:25:30,563 --> 00:25:33,690
until the election is over...

159
00:25:33,816 --> 00:25:36,318
and publicly announced.

160
00:25:40,573 --> 00:25:44,034
Could I at least get a cappuccino?
Not too hot!

161
00:25:45,703 --> 00:25:49,915
- What will we have?
- Orange juice.

162
00:25:51,793 --> 00:25:54,336
A cappuccino, very little froth.

163
00:26:11,938 --> 00:26:15,983
The Holy Father
has been seen by a physician...

164
00:26:16,109 --> 00:26:19,486
who said
he's in good physical condition.

165
00:26:19,571 --> 00:26:21,863
But the Holy Father isn't improving.

166
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:26,451
Given the gravity of the situation...

167
00:26:26,494 --> 00:26:28,704
the cardinals
said they're in favor of...

168
00:26:28,746 --> 00:26:31,248
Professor Brezzi,
may I present Cardinal Gregori.

169
00:26:31,374 --> 00:26:35,460
I know you, your picture
was in the papers.

170
00:26:35,503 --> 00:26:37,504
He was the front-runner, right?

171
00:26:37,630 --> 00:26:43,260
The cardinals are in favor
of trying psychoanalysis...

172
00:26:43,386 --> 00:26:48,140
despite the natural skepticism you can
well imagine. - Yes, I can imagine.

173
00:26:48,224 --> 00:26:54,021
I think it's unnecessary to remind you...

174
00:26:54,105 --> 00:26:59,610
- the concepts of soul and subconscious cannot possibly co-exist.
- Okay, we'll see.

175
00:26:59,652 --> 00:27:03,739
What's his name?
I don't recognize him.

176
00:27:03,781 --> 00:27:06,533
Who did you elect? What's his name?

177
00:27:06,618 --> 00:27:10,412
- Call him Holiness.
- It's a little too much!

178
00:27:10,538 --> 00:27:16,418
In a therapeutic situation,
a name can give life...

179
00:27:16,544 --> 00:27:18,378
to the relationship...

180
00:27:18,421 --> 00:27:22,299
Okay, it doesn't matter,
we cannot know his name.

181
00:27:22,383 --> 00:27:24,926
I'm off, I'll leave the two of you.

182
00:27:25,053 --> 00:27:28,680
- Where can the Pope and I meet?
- Here.

183
00:27:30,558 --> 00:27:33,060
Good morning.

184
00:27:33,144 --> 00:27:37,439
- How do you feel?
- I'm sorry, I don't know what to say.

185
00:27:37,565 --> 00:27:40,150
Don't worry.

186
00:27:40,193 --> 00:27:42,194
Fine, we'll begin now.

187
00:27:42,278 --> 00:27:44,946
Thank you all!

188
00:27:52,914 --> 00:27:55,082
Right...

189
00:27:55,208 --> 00:27:56,833
well...

190
00:27:59,045 --> 00:28:02,339
All that's happened recently...

191
00:28:02,423 --> 00:28:05,217
your election and everything...

192
00:28:05,343 --> 00:28:08,720
we'll lay it aside for the moment.

193
00:28:08,805 --> 00:28:13,934
I'd like us to begin with retracing...

194
00:28:13,976 --> 00:28:16,812
reliving your emotions...

195
00:28:16,854 --> 00:28:18,980
Wait.

196
00:28:21,109 --> 00:28:25,112
- I suppose I can't ask...
- Absolutely not.

197
00:28:25,196 --> 00:28:28,198
I was sure that anything about sex.

198
00:28:28,241 --> 00:28:30,325
A mention of his mother?

199
00:28:30,368 --> 00:28:34,871
Right now, it might reawaken
distant episodes, memories.

200
00:28:34,956 --> 00:28:36,998
- Exactly.
- Exactly?

201
00:28:37,083 --> 00:28:38,375
No.

202
00:28:38,501 --> 00:28:43,588
And what about facing unfulfilled
fantasies and desires?

203
00:28:43,631 --> 00:28:45,257
- No.
- No.

204
00:28:45,341 --> 00:28:47,843
Something regarding his childhood?

205
00:28:47,885 --> 00:28:50,011
With great discretion.

206
00:28:50,138 --> 00:28:52,139
With great discretion, fine.

207
00:28:52,223 --> 00:28:55,767
- Dreams, yes, though.
- It depends on the dreams.

208
00:28:55,893 --> 00:29:00,272
- However, no... it's best not to.
- Best not to...

209
00:29:00,356 --> 00:29:02,607
Perfect, thank you.

210
00:29:02,650 --> 00:29:04,276
Perfect.

211
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:06,403
Change of program!

212
00:29:06,529 --> 00:29:12,409
We'll start with
all that's happened recently.

213
00:29:12,493 --> 00:29:15,495
I just can't go on.

214
00:29:15,538 --> 00:29:18,915
Have you ever felt like this before?

215
00:29:20,126 --> 00:29:22,043
I don't know.

216
00:29:22,128 --> 00:29:24,796
I don't think so, but I don't know.

217
00:29:32,513 --> 00:29:34,681
Listen...

218
00:29:36,017 --> 00:29:39,186
- Any problems with your faith?
- No.

219
00:29:39,270 --> 00:29:41,688
- You're sure?
- Yes.

220
00:29:41,773 --> 00:29:44,316
God sees abilities in me
I don't have.

221
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:48,069
Where are these abilities?

222
00:29:48,154 --> 00:29:50,781
I look for them and find nothing.

223
00:29:50,823 --> 00:29:54,701
You've been chosen,
let's say, by God...

224
00:29:54,786 --> 00:29:57,412
for your qualities...

225
00:29:57,455 --> 00:29:59,039
for your goodness.

226
00:29:59,081 --> 00:30:02,042
So how can you possibly suddenly...

227
00:30:02,084 --> 00:30:04,961
Was the doctor asked
if he's a believer?

228
00:30:05,046 --> 00:30:06,797
No one asked.

229
00:30:06,839 --> 00:30:08,840
- Are you?
- No, I'm not.

230
00:30:08,925 --> 00:30:12,093
- Not good.
- But I'm afraid that's how it is.

231
00:30:12,220 --> 00:30:14,554
Anyway, let's go on.

232
00:30:14,597 --> 00:30:20,352
Excuse me, you can stay
it's fine, but in silence please!

233
00:30:20,478 --> 00:30:22,687
Your spokesman...

234
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:28,068
Your spokesman told me
that while they all waited for you...

235
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:31,863
- to go onto the balcony...
- Know what happened to me?

236
00:30:31,989 --> 00:30:37,244
- As they were coming towards me, some singing...
- Yes.

237
00:30:37,328 --> 00:30:40,121
Some crying...

238
00:30:40,206 --> 00:30:43,083
We were all very emotional.

239
00:30:43,125 --> 00:30:48,129
Little by little,
they began disappearing.

240
00:30:48,214 --> 00:30:50,507
They began disappearing?

241
00:30:50,591 --> 00:30:52,634
No...

242
00:30:52,718 --> 00:30:56,888
all the people I once knew
were suddenly gone.

243
00:30:56,973 --> 00:30:59,015
Everything vanished.

244
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:01,268
I can't remember anything.

245
00:31:10,278 --> 00:31:14,030
- Do you want to be Pope?
- I'm already Pope.

246
00:31:15,366 --> 00:31:17,659
It was decided by the cardinals.

247
00:31:18,619 --> 00:31:20,745
It was decided by God.

248
00:31:22,665 --> 00:31:25,625
Was this meeting of ours useful?

249
00:31:25,668 --> 00:31:26,793
I don't know.

250
00:31:26,878 --> 00:31:30,547
You see, Pope,
with all these people around...

251
00:31:30,673 --> 00:31:33,300
looking at me...

252
00:31:33,384 --> 00:31:35,677
checking me, I just can't work.

253
00:31:35,761 --> 00:31:40,181
Maybe a colleague
who doesn't know he's the Pope...

254
00:31:40,266 --> 00:31:45,020
could meet him away from here.

255
00:31:45,062 --> 00:31:48,815
We must do something right away.

256
00:31:48,941 --> 00:31:50,942
That's why we came to you.

257
00:31:51,068 --> 00:31:54,321
- Because you're the best.
- A curse!

258
